text: Nathan Law Kwun-chung (; born 13 July 1993) is a Hong Kong student leader, politician, activist and pro-democracy member. Alongside Joshua Wong, he led the 2014 Hong Kong protests.| Joshua Wong and Nathan Law released on bail from Hong Kong jail - CNN| Joshua Wong, Nathan Law and Alex Chow of the Umbrella Movement jailed for up to eight months SCMhttps://www.ft.com/content/d9b6bad6-b864-11e7-8c12-5661783e5589 | Hong Kong activists Joshua Wong and Nathan Law freed on bail He is the founding and former chairman of Demosistō. He founded Demosistō with Joshua Wong, Agnes Chow and more. On 30 June 2020, after the Hong Kong national security law was passed, he told the public on Facebook that he quits Demosistō. == Further reading == *Alex Chow *Joshua Wong *Agnes Chow == References == Category:1993 births Category:Living people Category:Hong Kong activists Category:21st-century Chinese politicians Category:Guangdong Category:Hong Kong politicians
